01325 |year= 1990 |accessdate= November 11, 2011}}\n* {{cite web |ref= harv |last= O'Connor |first= Tom |title= Constitutional Structure |url= http://www.drtomoconnor.com/3000/3000lect01.htm |year= 2010 |accessdate= November 14, 2011}}\n* {{cite book |ref= harv |last= Pritchett |first= C. Herman |title= The American Constitution |url= https://archive.org/details/americanconstitu0000prit_u5p8 |url-access= registration |publisher= McGraw-Hill |location= New York |year= 1959 }}\n* {{cite book |ref= harv |last= Qing Yu |first= Li |editor-last= Starr |editor-first= Joseph Barton |chapter= Dr. Sun Yat Sen and the U.S. Constitution |title= The United States Constitution: Its Birth, Growth, and Influence in Asia |publisher= Hong Kong University Press |location= Hong Kong |year= 1988 |isbn= 978-962-209-201-3 }}\n* {{cite book |ref= harv |editor-last= Stacy |editor-first= Lee |title= Mexico and the United States |volume= vol. 2 |publisher= Marshall Cavendish |location= London |year= 2003 |isbn= 978-0-7614-7402-9}}\n* {{cite book |ref= harv |last= Wood |first= Gordon |authorlink= Gordon S. Wood |title= The Creation of the American Republic, 1776\u20131787 |publisher= University of North Carolina Press |location= Chapel Hill |year= 1998 |isbn= 978-0-8078-4723-7 }}\n{{refend}}\n\n==Further reading==\n{{refbegin|30em}}\n* {{cite book |editorlink= Bernard Bailyn |editor-last= Bailyn |editor-first= Bernard |title= The Debate on the Constitution: Federalist and Antifederalist Speeches, Articles, and Letters During the Struggle for Ratification |volume= Part One: September 1787 to February 1788  |publisher= The Library of America|year= 1993}}\n* {{cite book |editor-last= Bailyn |editor-first= Bernard |title= The Debate on the Constitution: Federalist and Antifederalist Speeches, Articles, and Letters During the Struggle for Ratification |volume= Part Two: January to August 1788 |publisher= The Library of America |year= 1993 |isbn= 0-940450-64-X}}\n* {{cite book |authorlink= James Bryce, 1st Viscount Bryce |last=Bryce |first= James, viscount |title= The American Commonwealth |edition= 2nd |location= London |publisher= Macmillan and Co. |year= 1891 |volume= vol. 1 |pages= [350]\u2013397, [636]\u2013645, 669\u2013682, ''et passim''}}\n* {{cite journal |last= Casey |first= Gregory |title= The Supreme Court and Myth: An Empirical Investigation |journal= Law & Society Review |volume= 8 |issue= 3 |date= Spring 1974 |pages= 385\u2013420 |doi=10.2307/3053081|jstor= 3053081 }}\n* [[Donna Edwards|Edwards. Donna]], [[Mary Anne Franks]], David Law (Chair in Public Law at the [[University of Hong Kong]]), [[Lawrence Lessig]], and [[Louis Michael Seidman]], \"Constitution in Crisis: Has America's founding document become the nation's undoing?\", ''[[Harper's Magazine]]'', vol. 339, no. 2033 (October 2019), pp. 25\u201332. \"The Constitution is not producing a [[democracy]] that's responsive to the people. [p. 31.] ... How do we break this deeply unrepresentative system that we have right now?\" \"[O]ur system \u2013 and especially our elected leaders \u2013 are averse to change. But there is still a revolutionary spirit within the American public that doesn't exist among elected leaders.\" [p. 32.]\n* {{cite book |authorlink= Jonathan Elliot (historian) |last= Elliot |first= Jonathan |title= The Debates in the Several State Conventions of the Adoption of the Federal Constitution  |volume= Vol. 1, Constitution, Declaration of Independence, Articles of Confederation, Journal of Federal Convention, Vol. 2, State Conventions Massachusetts, Connecticut., New Hampshire, New York, Pennsylvania, Maryland, Vol. 3, Virginia, Vol. 4, North. and South. Carolina, Resolutions, Tariffs, Banks, Debt, Vol. 5 Debates in Congress, Madison's Notes, Misc. Letters}}\n* {{cite book |editorlink= Paul Leicester Ford |editor-last= Ford |editor-first= Paul Leicester |title= Pamphlets on the Constitution of the United States, Published During its Discussion by the People, 1787\u20131788