===Coaching staff===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! Name !! Position !! Year at Ole Miss !! [[Alma mater]] (Year)\n|-\n|[[Hugh Freeze]]||Head Coach||5th||[[Southern Mississippi University|Southern Miss]] (1992)\n|-\n|[[Matt Luke (American football)|Matt Luke]]||Assistant Head Coach/Co-Offensive Coordinator/Offensive Line||5th||[[University Of Mississippi|Ole Miss]] (2000)\n|-\n|Dan Werner||Co-Offensive Coordinator/Quarterbacks||5th||[[Western Michigan University|Western Michigan]] (1983)\n|-\n|Maurice Harris||Tight Ends/Recruiting Coordinator For Offense||5th||[[Arkansas State University|Arkansas State]] (1998)\n|-\n|Grant Heard||Wide Receivers||5th||[[University Of Mississippi|Ole Miss]] (2001)\n|-\n|Derrick Nix||Running Backs||9th||[[Southern Mississippi University|Southern Miss]] (2002)\n|-\n|Jason Jones||Co-Defensive Coordinator/Cornerbacks||4th||[[University of Alabama|Alabama]] (2001)\n|-\n|Dave Wommack||Associate Head Coach for Defense/Co-Defensive Coordinator/Linebackers||5th||[[Missouri Southern State University|Missouri Southern State]] (1978)\n|-\n|Chris Kiffin||Defensive Line/Recruiting Coordinator For Defense||5th||[[Colorado State University|Colorado State]] (2005)\n|-\n|Corey Batoon\n|Special Teams Coach/Safeties\n|2nd\n|[[California State University, Long Beach|Long Beach State]] (1991)\n|-\n|Paul Jackson||Head Strength & Conditioning Coach||5th||[[Montclair State University|Montclair State]] (2006)\n|}\n\n==Schedule==\nOle Miss announced its 2016 football schedule on October 29, 2015. The 2016 schedule consists of 7 home games, 5 away games and 1 neutral site game in the regular season. The Rebels will host SEC foes [[Alabama Crimson Tide football|Alabama]], [[Auburn Tigers football|Auburn]], [[Georgia Bulldogs football|Georgia]], and [[Mississippi State Bulldogs football|Mississippi State]], and will travel to [[Arkansas Razorbacks football|Arkansas]], [[LSU Tigers football|LSU]], [[Texas A&M Aggies football|Texas A&M]], and [[Vanderbilt Commodores football|Vanderbilt]].<ref name=\"UM16\">{{cite press release|url=http://www.olemisssports.com/sports/m-footbl/spec-rel/102915aaa.html|title=2016 Ole Miss Football Schedule Announced|publisher=University of Mississippi Department of Athletics|date=October 29, 2015|accessdate=October 30, 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe Rebels hosted three of its four non\u2013conference games against [[Georgia Southern Eagles football|Georgia Southern]] from the [[Sun Belt Conference]], [[Memphis Tigers football|Memphis]] from the [[American Athletic Conference]] and [[Wofford Terriers football|Wofford]] from the [[Southern Conference]]. Ole Miss started the season at a neutral site in [[Orlando, Florida]] on [[Labor Day]] against [[Florida State Seminoles football|Florida State]] of the [[Atlantic Coast Conference]].\n{{CFB schedule\n| rankyear = 2016\n| poll = [[2016 NCAA Division I FBS football rankings#AP Poll|AP Poll]] released prior to game.\n| seasonsource = fbschedules.com<ref>{{cite web |title=2016 Ole Miss Rebels Football Schedule|url=http://www.fbschedules.com/ncaa-16/2016-ole-miss-rebels-football-schedule.php|publisher=FB Schedules|accessdate=October 30, 2015}}</ref>\n| timezone = Central\n\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 5\n| time = 7:00 p.m.\n| w/l = l\n| nonconf = y\n| neutral = y\n| rank = 11\n| opponent = [[2016 Florida State Seminoles football team|Florida State]]\n| opprank = 4\n| gamename = [[Camping World Kickoff]]\n| site_stadium = [[Camping World Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Orlando, Florida]]\n| tv = [[ESPN College Football|ESPN]]\n| score = {{URL|1=http://www.espn.com/college-football/recap?gameId=400868979|2=34\u201345}}\n| attend = 63,042\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 10\n| time = 3:00 p.m.\n| w/l = v\n| nonconf = y\n| rank = 19\n| opponent = [[2016 Wofford Terriers football team|Wofford]]\n| site_stadium = [[Vaught\u2013Hemingway Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Oxford, Mississippi]]\n| tv = [[SEC Network|SECN]]\n|